  "texts": [
    "Our random forest regression models presented a good level of accuracy during the training phase.",
    "Nonetheless, the results could be improved by a greater number of in situ observations of soil P fractions and other edaphic and climatic variables in the Amazon region, especially in high-elevation areas where observations are lacking, with notable exceptions (Wilcke et al., 2019).",
    "The P forms have different residence times ranging from hours to millennia and are subject to a complex set of interactions with biotic, edaphic, and climatic environmental attributes over time.",
    "In this scenario, the presented maps can be useful to define initial conditions to dynamic, process-oriented models, for the simulation of P cycling in soils (Helfenstein et al., 2018).",
    "Finally, it is important to note that our P maps rely on raster datasets used to predict the P pools, which are subject to their own uncertainties (Poggio et al., 2021)."
  ],
